paragraph.keyLead:
- Fully winged, or micropterous, or brachypterous, or apterous; fore wing of fully winged forms with costal and 1–2 further basal cells clearly enclosed by pigmented veins (Plate 3B, C); occasionally fore wing with only costal cell clearly enclosed by pigmented veins, but then occipital carina absent (in some males of 
Gonatopodinae
)................................ 2

- Fully winged, or rarely micropterous, or brachypterous, or apterous; fore wing of fully winged forms with costal, median and submedian cells clearly enclosed by pigmented veins (Plate 3C); occasionally only costal cell clearly enclosed by pigmented veins, but then occipital carina absent (in some males of 
Gonatopodinae
)......................................... 4
